verses.roman:
yamunāte jala-keli gopī-gaṇa-saṅge
kṛṣṇa karena--mahāprabhu magna sei raṅge

synonyms: yamunāte—in the River Yamunā; jala-keli—pastimes in the water; gopī-gaṇa-saṅge—with the gopīs; kṛṣṇa karena—Kṛṣṇa performs; mahāprabhu—Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu; magna—fully merged; sei raṅge—in those pastimes.
translation: Lord Kṛṣṇa performed pastimes with the gopīs in the waters of the Yamunā, and Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu fully merged in those pastimes.
